author: syracuse.com | The Post-Standard
title: Super DIRT Week 2015: Live updates from time trials for 358-modifieds, big-block modifieds
text:
Syracuse, N.Y. — It's a big day at the Syracuse Mile with the cars hitting the track at the New York State Fairgrounds for time trials on Thursday.
The action continues tonight at Brewerton Speedway with the Hurricane 100.
You can follow along in the comments section all day long.
THURSDAY 8 a.m.—Pit Gates Open
8 a.m.—Inspection for All Divisions (pit road turn four side -inspection tent)
9 a.m.—Super DIRTcar Big Block Modified Series, DIRTcar 358-Modified Series Draw Opens at Series Command Center
10 a.m.—Grandstands Open
10 a.m.-10:55 a.m.—Super DIRTcar Big Block Modified Series practice
11 a.m.-11:55 a.m.—DIRTcar 358-Modified Series Practice
Noon—Media Day' Press Conference-Infield Conference Building "John Hill Media Center"
1:20 p.m.—DIRTcar 358-Modified Time Trials (2-laps, Top-6 Qualify for Front-3 Rows) Qualifying Order Placement based on Practice Times Slowest to Fastest Time
2:45 p.m.—Super DIRTcar Big Block Modified Series Time Trials (2-laps, Top-6 Qualify for Front-3 Rows) Qualifying Order Placement based on Practice Times Slowest to Fastest Time
3:45 p.m.-3:55 p.m.—DIRTcar 358-Modified Futures Practice/Qualifying
4 p.m.-4:10 p.m.—DIRTcar Sportsman Futures Practice/Qualifying
4:15 p.m.- 4:25 p.m.—DIRTcar Pro Stocks Futures Practice/Qualifying
4:30 p.m.-4:40 p.m.—DIRTcar Big Blocks Futures Practice/Qualifying
7:30 p.m.—DIRTcar 358-Modified Series at 23nd Annual "Hurricane 100" Brewerton Speedway
10 p.m.—Pit Area Closed (NYSF)
Rubber hits the road at Super DIRT Week There were two hours devoted to practice laps at the Syracuse Mile for the big-block modifieds at the fairgrounds.
